class Solution {
    public boolean validPalindrome(String s) {
        int left = 0, right = s.length() - 1;
        while (left < right) {
            if (s.charAt(left) != s.charAt(right)) {
                return isPalindrome(s, left + 1, right) || isPalindrome(s, left, right - 1);
            }
            left++;
            right--;
        }
        return true;
    }

    private boolean isPalindrome(String s, int l, int r) {
        while (l < r) {
            if (s.charAt(l++) != s.charAt(r--)) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Two-pointer scan from both ends; on the first mismatch, check both possible single deletions (skip left or skip right) via a helper that verifies the remaining substring is a palindrome. Only one extra pass is needed in the worst case, keeping memory usage constant.

